Row - Class in tableTemplate
A Row Class that can be instantiated to define the style of the table and build the table for the use in printf.

Default Constructor used to initialize a Row with default values.
rowBuilder(int, Cell...) - Method in class tableTemplate.Row
Method to generate an heterogeneous tables.
rowBuilder(Cell...) - Method in class tableTemplate.Row
Method that construct a row based on the cells passed.
rowBuilder(Cell, int, int) - Method in class tableTemplate.Row
This method is used to construct homogeneous tables.
RowConfiguration - Enum Class in tableTemplate
Defines the possible configurations for a Row. - Separator: The character between each column of the table. - Corner: The corners of the table - Boundary: The upper and lower boundary of the row.
rowFinalBoundaryBuilder(int) - Method in class tableTemplate.Row
Method used to create the final boundary of the table if needed.
